@KostyaSha as people use this in production environments are and are being hit by this bug, I think it would be prudent to have a unit test to cover this issue.
1. To test out the current fix and make sure you does what you think it does.
2. To prevent this issue from occurring again in the future when someone who doesn't understand the code changes something non-obvious.

